My situation is somewhat similar. I need to set up a new website, and I'm currently organizing my requirements regarding accessibility and privacy (so no tools like Google Analytics), and researching how to make video calls using Signal; this requires a lot of customer education! But I think it's worth it.
@user4 @user3 You can definitely do it! I'd be happy to share my experience with you.
Website: You can check out @user5. It looks easy to use, has a nice interface, and is open source. I plan to migrate one of my websites to it before my next renewal.
Signal: Check out cal.com. It's an open source calendar service that integrates scheduling for video calls with Element, JITSI, etc. It also supports Signal, but I haven't tested yet whether it can only send messages or also supports video calls.
I can recommend @user6. End-to-end encryption, decentralized, open source.
